<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Tired of killing four hundred monsters to gain a level?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Anonymous">Anonymous</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:04 p.m. 7/8/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Tired of killing four hundred monsters to gain a level?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>This information is put out as general knowledge. Use it at your own risks as to what the consiquences might be.

<P>In EverQuest, anyone who's played know's that the game is constantly making you have to gain levels in order to get any fun out of it. Several methods have been used but one of the best so far is to simply block a higher level monster behind an object and then cast magic on it from a distance, never letting it hit you.
<BR>For players that are in LavaStorm Mountains, you can trap a monster near the entrance to zone to Najena. If you are standing outside the cave entrance, looking towards the door, on the left hand side is a mountain ridge. You can climb the mountain ridge, target a monster, cast a spell upon him, and then run towards the entrance to Najena. If you follow the cliff around and then go through the door about half way up, the monster will continue to travel up, while you are safely inside of the cave. You always have to come from the left side of the door. Now your going to fall and hurt yourself a little, but hitpoints don't matter when you can't get hit. This takes a little practice and you might not get it right away. Have fun with this, as the game was designed for.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
